果壳。
Fruit shells.
科学和技术，是我们和这个世界对话所用的语言。
Science and technology are the language of our dialogue with the world.
。
.
很多来香港旅游的游客，都会到访维多利亚湾打卡拍照。
Many visitors to Hong Kong come to Victoria Bay to have their cards taken.
不知道大家是否曾留意到湾仔海旁一栋栋高耸的楼宇？这当中，位于添马舰的香港政府总部大楼最引人注目，因为它好似一个巨大的门洞。
I wonder if you have ever noticed the towering buildings along the Wan Chai waterfront, among which the Hong Kong government headquarters building on the Tamar is the most striking because it looks like a huge doorway.
为什么要设计这么一个大洞呢？原因要从17年前的那场非典型肺炎（SARS）疫情谈起。
Why design such a large hole? The reason is to start with the SARS outbreak 17 years ago.
香港维多利亚湾旁的添马舰香港政府总部 | 搜狐香港：高密度超大城市的挑战香港地势崎岖，山地面积占82%，可供发展的平地相当稀缺，居住环境紧迫。
Hong Kong: High Density Mega-City Challenge Hong Kong has a rugged terrain of 82%. Flats available for development are scarce and living in an urgent environment.
也正是这一原因，奠定香港今日高密度城市发展的模式。
It is for this reason that Hong Kong today enjoys a high density of urban development.
目前面积1100平方公里的土地上，居住着748万居民，每年访港游客高达6515万人次[1]。
At present, 7.48 million people live on an area of 1,100 square kilometres, with 65.15 million visitors a year; 1 & # 93;
市区平均每平方公里约为6000人，而在居住密度最高的区域观塘可达15000人[2]。
Urban areas have an average of about 6,000 people per square kilometre, and Kwun Tong has the highest occupancy rate at 15000 or # 91; 2 & # 93;
俯瞰香港城区密集的建筑群 | 图虫创意2003年对于香港人来说是难以忘怀的，因为SARS这一高传染性疾病在香港社区爆发，在2003年2月至6月短短四个月造成1755人染病，导致299人死亡[3]。
The year 2003 was a memorable year for Hong Kong people, as SARS, a highly contagious disease that struck Hong Kong's community, infected 1,755 people in just four months between February and June 2003, causing 299 deaths and # 91; 3 and 93;
世界卫生组织认为香港的人口密度高，地区之间没有明显的界线划分，是最难控制疫情的城市之一。
The World Health Organisation considers Hong Kong one of the most difficult cities to control because of its high population density and the lack of sharp regional boundaries.
SARS对香港的经济、民生、政治各方面均影响深远，特别是公共卫生意识的提高。
SARS has had a profound impact on Hong Kong's economy, people's livelihood and politics, especially the raising of public health awareness.
时至今日，香港居民平时若有头疼脑热都会自觉戴口罩，出入常洗手，医院、政府、学校都会配备有酒精消毒液和口罩，各楼宇电梯、门、扶手等均采取每小时清洁消毒一次的措施。
Today, Hong Kong residents wear face masks and wash their hands frequently. Hospitals, governments and schools are equipped with alcohol disinfectant and face masks. Every building lift, door and handrail is cleaned and disinfected every hour.
2004年香港卫生署开展的个人及环境卫生调查显示：“在SARS爆发后，受访者表示他们的个人卫生(61.6%)、家居卫生(56.8%)，以及香港整体环境卫生(80.0%)均有改善。
According to the Personal and Environmental Hygiene Survey conducted by the Department of Health in 2004, "Following the outbreak of SARS, respondents indicated that their personal hygiene (61.6%), household hygiene (56.8%) and overall environmental hygiene in Hong Kong (80.0%) improved.
”[4]除去公共卫生改善措施，政府和设计人员也意识到建筑环境品质和气候要素对市民健康及环境卫生的重要性，开始了长达十几年的改善城市规划和建筑设计的变革[5]。
In addition to public health improvements, the Government and designers, aware of the importance of building environmental quality and climate factors to people's health and environmental health, have begun a decade of change and # 91; 5 & # 93; & # 39; s improvements in urban planning and architecture.
首先由香港政府行政长官挂帅开展全城清洁策划小组，2003年8月公布了《全城清洁策划小组报告-改善香港环境卫生措施》，其中提出三个方面的重点改善：在建筑物设计方面重新审视和改善排水渠和通风系统的设计；在城市设计方面提升城市规划，特别针对大型规划和发展项目开展空气流通评估，开设通风和景观廊；在公共屋邨提供更多绿化和休闲用地[6]。
In August 2003, the Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Government launched a citywide Clean Planning Group Report - Measures to Improve Environmental Hygiene in Hong Kong. The report outlines three key improvements: re-examining and improving the design of drains and ventilation systems in building design; urban planning, particularly air ventilation and landscaping for large-scale planning and development projects; and greening and leisure land and landscaping at public rental housing estates.
随后政府推出多项有关城市气候与环境的顾问项目，颁布多项相关技术通告和设计指引，逐步将城市气候评估科学研究成果应用到城市规划及建筑设计当中。
Subsequently, the Government launched a number of consultancy projects on urban climate and the environment, and issued a number of related technical circulars and design guidelines to gradually apply the results of scientific research on urban climate assessment to urban planning and building design.
从城市规划和建筑设计入手，让风流进城市让我们再回到开篇提及的位于维多利亚湾的添马舰政府总部大楼。
Starting with urban planning and architecture, let's get wind of the city and let's go back to the Tamar Government Headquarters building in Victoria Bay.
为什么建筑设计中会开一个大洞？这是因为香港规划署因应SARS而推出的《空气流通评估方法》[7-8]， 为避免一字排开的屏风楼设计阻挡空气流通，在政府总部大楼设计这类大型建筑项目，要求不仅考虑了自身楼宇的通风需求，还要尽量减低对周边区域的风环境影响，确保整个街区的空气流通。
Why is there a large hole in the building design? This is because the Air Ventilation Assessment Method introduced by the Planning Department in response to SARS? To avoid lining-up screen buildings designed to block air flow, large-scale building projects such as the Government Secretariat Building are designed to minimise wind impact on the surrounding area and ensure ventilation throughout the block.
因为政府总部大楼位于海旁，比较开阔又有良好的海风，而建筑基地后面紧邻港岛主要的交通枢纽区域，来往人流和车流非常多，为了利于海风渗透入后面的稠密市区就需要在建筑物上开设空洞，让体量巨大的建筑有更好的风渗透性，并确保地面有开敞的绿地空间连接海滨。
As the Government Secretariat Building is located on the waterfront and is relatively open and windy, the construction site is located in the immediate vicinity of Hong Kong Island's main traffic hub and there is a large traffic flow and traffic. To facilitate sea breezes to penetrate the dense urban areas behind it, it is necessary to open holes in the buildings to provide better wind permeability to large buildings and to ensure open green space to connect the waterfront.
当时建筑立面上这个孔洞到底怎么放置、开多大、朝向如何，都经过了计算机模拟及风洞试验来确定。
At that time, how the hole on the vertical surface of the building, how large, how oriented, have been computer simulation and wind tunnel tests to determine.
香港添马舰政府总部 | 搜狐利用风洞试验和流体力学模拟来测算拟建建筑物的设计对于周边风环境的评估 | 香港规划署随后，香港政府于2006-2012年全面评估城市环境及居民人体舒适度，开展了《都市气候图及风环境评估标准》项目[9-10]。
Hong Kong's Tamar Government Secretariat & # 124; Sohu uses wind tunnel tests and hydrodynamic simulations to calculate the design of a proposed building. Next, the Hong Kong government conducted a comprehensive assessment of the urban environment and residents' physical comfort in 2006-2012.
目前香港涉及的新区规划、旧城改造都考虑了城市风环境评估、城市热岛效应、室外人体舒适度评估、通风廊道等。
At present, urban wind environment assessment, urban heat island effect, outdoor body comfort assessment, ventilation corridor etc. are considered in the planning of new areas and urban renewal in Hong Kong.
下图为古洞北新发展区规划和预留出来的通风走廊。
The following image shows the ventilation corridors planned and reserved for the new development area of Kwu Tung North.
古洞北新发展区通风走廊 | 香港政府（2015）另外为了推广研究成果，香港政府规划署更新《香港规划标准与准则-第十一章：城市设计指引》，利用图示的方法向规划师、建筑师和普通大众介绍改善空气流通的设计措施，涉及建筑物形态与布局控制、街道方向、建筑群房和高度控制、绿地开敞空间配置等[11]。
In addition, to promote its findings, the Planning Department has updated the Hong Kong Planning Standards and Guidelines - Chapter 11: Urban Design Guidelines to inform planners, architects and the general public about design measures to improve air ventilation, including building form and layout control, street direction, block building and height control, and green open space configuration & # 91; 11 & # 93;
具体措施譬如：城市街道的方向应顺应主要风向，最多不可以超过30度角的倾斜，这样有利风入城。
Specific measures such as: the direction of urban streets should follow the main wind direction, up to a maximum angle of 30 degrees tilt, so that the wind into the city.
再如在海旁的新建建筑物时，应确保不同建筑之间留有一定的间距，便于海风渗透至内陆地区，避免形成一字排开屏风似的遮挡。
In the case of new buildings along the waterfront, it is important to ensure that there is a certain amount of space between the different buildings so that the sea breeze can penetrate inland and avoid creating a screen-like barrier.
香港城市设计指引-摘要 | 香港政府规划署（2005)随后，香港政府屋宇署委托研究团队开展优化都市生活环境的可持续性，检讨了香港建筑法规条例及实际运作中有关涉城市生活空间品质的问题，针对新建楼宇提出三个关键指引：控制楼宇之间的透风度促使城市内部空气流通、窄街后退确保行人区域的空气流通，提高楼盘内的绿化覆盖率以改善微气候环境及舒缓城市热岛效应，并编制出《APP151-优化建筑设计　缔造可持续建筑环境》及《APP152-可持续建筑设计指引》两个供专业人士使用的建筑设计指引[12]。
Urban Design Guidelines - Summary & # 124; Planning Department (2005). Subsequently, the Buildings Department commissioned a research team to optimize the sustainability of the urban living environment. Three key guidelines were proposed for new buildings: air ventilation in Hong Kong's building codes and practices, air ventilation in narrow streets, greening of buildings to improve the microclimate environment and alleviate urban heat island effects, and APP151 - Optimizing Architectural Design for a Sustainable Building.
值得一提的是，这个指引首次针对香港高密度高层建筑居多的状况将建筑高度分为低层区（0-20m），中层区（20-60m）及高层区（60m以上）评估区域，每个层区都有具体针对楼宇间距和空洞的定量计算要求。
It is worth noting that this guideline for the first time targets the high-density high-rise buildings in Hong Kong, where the height of the building is divided into low-rise areas (0-20 m), mid-level areas (20-60 m) and high-rise areas (above 60 m). Each zone has specific quantitative calculation requirements for building spacing and voids.
楼宇透风度计算及示意图[12]防控疫病，城市建设不容忽视我作为政府空气流通评估的顾问，在过去十几年间参与多项国内外政府的城市环境顾问研究项目。
As a consultant to the Government for air ventilation assessment, I have participated in a number of government urban environmental consultancy projects over the past decade or so.
城市规划方案的有效期短则十年，可长达数十年，甚至百年。
Urban planning programmes can be as short as 10 years, and can be decades or even centuries.
一旦出错，大拆大建又浪费人力物力。
When mistakes are made, big construction wastes manpower and material resources.
SARS和此次新冠肺炎传染病疫情的爆发，再次把如何更好规划百万人口城市，提供健康生活环境提到我们面前。
SARS and the outbreak of the New Crown Pneumonia epidemic have once again raised the question of how best to plan for a city of one million people and provide a healthy living environment.
值得我们审视城市居住环境中最基本的自然环境和气候因素，确保日照、通风、排水等基本规划设计指标符合卫生健康保障。
It is worth examining the most basic natural environment and climatic factors in the urban living environment to ensure that the basic planning and design indicators such as sunshine, ventilation and drainage accord with the health and safety guarantee.
如何更好规划百万人口城市，提供健康生活环境？| Pixabay在经历了SARS之后，香港城市规划与建筑设计针对城市通风和空气流通给与高度重视，积极考虑利用管控城市空间规划，加强市区稠密地区通风廊道和绿地开敞空间的配置，并且从立体空间分层的角度管控建筑形态，做到更通透更有利于空气流通，改善户外空气品质和舒适宜居[13-14]。
After SARS, Hong Kong's urban planning and architecture gave high priority to urban ventilation and ventilation, actively considering the use of urban spatial planning to enhance ventilation corridors and open spaces in densely populated urban areas, and to improve ventilation, outdoor air quality and comfort & # 91; 13-14 & # 93 from the perspective of spatial stratification.
面对气候变化，频繁的交通联系、高密度人群和超大的城市建设，也许未来还会有其他新型传染病或其他灾害的出现，迫切需要思考和研究城市规划的空间品质对公众健康风险的关联和影响。
In the face of climate change, frequent traffic links, high density of people and mega-urban construction, there may be other emerging infectious diseases or other disasters in the future. There is an urgent need to consider and study the relevance and impact of the spatial quality of urban planning on public health risks.
